        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Since the discussion seems to continue here rather than in issues, I'll copy my remark from https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39307#issuecomment-4296647058 :\r\n\r\nWhile `g:health` is a temporary \"fix\" as you put it, it's handy to configure the aspect of `:checkhealth` system-wide. It can be complementary to `:float` (which I did not know about).\r\n\r\nCompare it to `'winborder'`: yes, you can specify `{..., border = 'single', ...}` in every call which opens a new window, but it's much easier to specify it once and for all, with the option to override it on a single call.\r\n\r\nThe form of `g:health` might need to change, but having the option to have a configurable default should still be available without prepending `:float` to every command I might call as a user.",
