        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`make_floating_popup_options` only added support for `relative='editor'` because of `g:health`. Originally it wasn’t designed to support this.  https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/b12b91c2743954dbe8599caa60e58e5d74aa4e76\r\n\r\nWhen `g:health` added, we didn’t have the `:float` modifier, so using a global like `g:health` made sense at the time.      `:checkhealth` is only used occasionally when something is wrong 🤔  usage frequency should be quite low, so it’s probably not worth adding extra complexity for this and also isn’t much need for extensibility here. border are already handled by `winborder`.   closing behavior wouldn’t need extra autocmds when we have `float`, if curwin is a preview window, we could just close it directly in win_goto.  So I think using the `float` modifier would be simpler, and it could be useful in other places as well. That said, I don’t have a strong preference either way.\r\n",
            "created_at": "2026-04-23T08:05:11Z",
